,"1126":"1126","1125":"1125","1202":"1202","BET 1187 AND 1202":"fra 1187 til 1202","1155":"1155","1088":"1088","about 1126":"omkring 1126","1240":"1240","Ukraine":"Ukraine"},"nl":{"about 1126–BET 1187 AND 1202":"circa 1126–van 1187 to 1202","1126–1202":"1126–1202","1155–1240":"1155–1240","1088–1125":"1088–1125","Aft 1125":"na 1125","1126":"1126","1125":"1125","1202":"1202","BET 1187 AND 1202":"van 1187 to 1202","1155":"1155","1088":"1088","about 1126":"circa 1126","1240":"1240","Ukraine":"Oekraïne"},"en":{"about 1126–BET 1187 AND 1202":"about 1126–from 1187 to 1202","1126–1202":"1126–1202","1155–1240":"1155–1240","1088–1125":"1088–1125","Aft 1125":"after 1125","1126":"1126","1125":"1125","1202":"1202","BET 1187 AND 1202":"from 1187 to 1202","1155":"1155","1088":"1088","about 1126":"about 1126","1240":"1240","Ukraine":"Ukraine","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Khan","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Arabic/Muslim Mohammad, Mohammed, Abdul, Muhammad, Mohamed, Bibi, Tariq, Ali, Asif, Khalid, Amir, Saeed.","Muslim (also common among African Americans): from <i>khan</i>, an English spelling of a status name based on Mongolian <i>khaan</i> ‘(military) ruler, sovereign’. This was originally a hereditary title among Tartar and Mongolian tribesmen (in particular Genghis Khan, 1162–1227), but is now very widely used throughout the Muslim world as a surname. In Iran and parts of the Indian subcontinent it is used as an honorific title after a person's name."],"variants":[{"name":"Khanom","meanings":["Muslim (Bangladesh and Iran): from Persian <i>khānum</i> ‘princess, noblewoman’. This is not actually a surname, but a female honorific, the feminine equivalent of   Khan  . Compare   Khanam  ."]}]},{"name":"Of","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Korean Kyong, Kyong Suk, Young, Chae, Chi Young, Hang, Kil, Rin, Sang Hun, Chang, Chong, Insoo, Kum, Sun Young, Yom, Young Hwan.  Cambodian Kiwan, Oeurn, Phoeun, Pich, Saroeuth, Seung, Sophath, Sophea, Yoeun, Phan, Son.  Indian Shanti, Harendra.","Indian (Uttar Pradesh): Brahmin name, from Sanskrit <i>om</i>, the Hindu sacred and mystic syllable uttered at the beginning of prayers.","Cambodian: written ឱម, corresponding to the exclamation of solemn affirmation, of Sanskrit origin (see 1 above), chanted by Buddhist monks."],"variants":[{"name":"Oum","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Southeast Asian Heang, Hye, Kam, Kan, Kheng, Khin, Kun, Sang, Sok, Phong, Yom, Yoo, Youn, Cuong, Phal, Samnang, Tin.  Cambodian Sokha, Chheang, Choeun, Moeun, Roeun, Sambath, Samoeun, Savuth, Soeun, Sopheap.","Cambodian: written អ៊ុំ, from a Khmer word denoting an elder sibling of one's parent (i.e. ‘uncle’ or ‘aunt’). Compare   Om   3 and   Um   2."]}]},{"name":"The","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Vietnamese: unexplained.","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surname 鄭, possibly based on its Hokkien or Teochew pronunciation, see   Zheng   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Zheng","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Jian, Yi, Bin, Hong, Hua, Li, Wei, Yong, Ting, Xin, Yan, Hui, Min, Hao, Shen, Da, Quan, Tian, Chong.","Chinese:","Mandarin form of the surname 鄭: from Zheng (鄭), the name of a state (located in part of present-day Shaanxi and Henan provinces) granted to You, the younger brother of King Xuan of Zhou (reigned 827–782  BC ). The state of Zheng was annexed by the state of Han (located in present-day Shaanxi and Henan provinces) during the Warring States period (475–221  BC )."]}]},{"name":"Cumans","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Cummings  .","Dutch: variant of <b>Coomans</b>, <b>Coopmans</b> and   Koopmans  , a genitivized occupational name from <i>koopman</i> ‘merchant’."],"variants":[{"name":"Cummings","meanings":["Scottish and English (of Norman origin): variant of   Cumming  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Konchek Otrakovich Khan Of The Cumans was born about 1126, in Ukraine as the son of Otrok Atraka Kipchaks. He had at least 1 son. He died from 1187 to 1202."},"et":{"about 1126–BET 1187 AND 1202":"umbes 1126–1187 kuni 1202","1126–1202":"1126–1202","1155–1240":"1155–1240","1088–1125":"1088–1125","Aft 1125":"pärast 1125","1126":"1126","1125":"1125","1202":"1202","BET 1187 AND 1202":"1187 kuni 1202","1155":"1155","1088":"1088","about 1126":"umbes 1126","1240":"1240","Ukraine":"Ukraina"},"fi":{"about 1126–BET 1187 AND 1202":"noin 1126–vuodesta 1187 vuoteen 1202","1126–1202":"1126–1202","1155–1240":"1155–1240","1088–1125":"1088–1125","Aft 1125":"1125 jälkeen","1126":"1126","1125":"1125","1202":"1202","BET 1187 AND 1202":"vuodesta 1187 vuoteen 1202","1155":"1155","1088":"1088","about 1126":"noin 1126","1240":"1240","Ukraine":"Ukraina"},"fr":{"about 1126–BET 1187 AND 1202":"environ 1126–du 1187 au 1202","1126–1202":"1126–1202","1155–1240":"1155–1240","1088–1125":"1088–1125","Aft 1125":"après 1125","1126":"1126","1125":"1125","1202":"1202","BET 1187 AND 1202":"du 1187 au 1202","1155":"1155","1088":"1088","about 1126":"environ 1126","1240":"1240","Ukraine":"Ukraine","lifeSummary":"Konchek Otrakovich Khan Of The Cumans est né environ 1126, à Ukraine, fils de Otrok Atraka Kipchaks. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé du 1187 au 1202."},"de":{"about 1126–BET 1187 AND 1202":"um 1126–von 1187 bis 1202","1126–1202":"1126–1202","1155–1240":"1155–1240","1088–1125":"1088–1125","Aft 1125":"nach 1125","1126":"1126","1125":"1125","1202":"1202","BET 1187 AND 1202":"von 1187 bis 1202","1155":"1155","1088":"1088","about 1126":"um 1126","1240":"1240","Ukraine":"Ukraine","lifeSummary":"Konchek Otrakovich Khan Of The Cumans wurde um 1126 in Ukraine, als Sohn von O